---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "Terms of Service | My-Fi";
const description = "Read My-Fi's terms of service to understand the rules and guidelines for using our AI-powered personal finance advisory platform.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalUrl="/terms">
  <section class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-header">
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2025</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>By accessing or using My-Fi ("the Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, please do not use the Service.</p>
          <p>We may modify these Terms at any time. Your continued use of the Service after any changes constitutes acceptance of the new Terms.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Description of Service</h2>
          <p>My-Fi is an AI-powered personal finance advisory platform that provides personalized financial guidance and educational information to users. The Service includes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Personalized financial advice based on user-provided information</li>
            <li>Educational content about budgeting, saving, investing, and Canadian tax optimization</li>
            <li>Tools and calculators to help with financial planning</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Important Disclaimer</h2>
          <div class="disclaimer-box">
            <p><strong>My-Fi provides educational financial information and personalized guidance, NOT professional financial, tax, or legal advice.</strong></p>
            <p>The information provided by My-Fi is for general informational and educational purposes only. It should not be considered as a substitute for advice from a qualified financial advisor, accountant, or attorney.</p>
            <p>Before making any significant financial decisions, we recommend consulting with licensed professionals who can evaluate your specific circumstances.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>User Accounts</h2>
          <h3>Account Creation</h3>
          <p>To use certain features of the Service, you must create an account. You agree to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide accurate and complete information during registration</li>
            <li>Maintain the security of your account credentials</li>
            <li>Notify us immediately of any unauthorized access to your account</li>
            <li>Accept responsibility for all activities under your account</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Account Termination</h3>
          <p>We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your account at any time for violation of these Terms or for any other reason at our discretion.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>User Responsibilities</h2>
          <p>When using My-Fi, you agree to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide accurate financial information to receive relevant advice</li>
            <li>Use the Service only for lawful purposes</li>
            <li>Not attempt to circumvent any security features</li>
            <li>Not use the Service to harm, harass, or defraud others</li>
            <li>Not reverse engineer or attempt to access the underlying code</li>
            <li>Not use automated systems to access the Service without permission</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>The Service, including its content, features, and functionality, is owned by My-Fi and is protected by Canadian and international copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws.</p>
          <p>You may not reproduce, distribute, modify, or create derivative works from any part of the Service without our prior written consent.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>My-Fi is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind</li>
            <li>We do not guarantee the accuracy, completeness, or usefulness of any information provided</li>
            <li>We are not liable for any financial losses or damages resulting from your use of the Service or reliance on information provided</li>
            <li>Our total liability shall not exceed the amount you paid for the Service in the past 12 months</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Indemnification</h2>
          <p>You agree to indemnify and hold harmless My-Fi, its officers, directors, employees, and agents from any claims, damages, losses, or expenses arising from your use of the Service or violation of these Terms.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Governing Law</h2>
          <p>These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Province of Ontario and the federal laws of Canada applicable therein, without regard to conflict of law principles.</p>
          <p>Any disputes arising from these Terms or your use of the Service shall be resolved in the courts of Ontario, Canada.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Severability</h2>
          <p>If any provision of these Terms is found to be unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Contact Information</h2>
          <p>If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us at:</p>
          <p>
            <strong>My-Fi Legal Team</strong><br>
            Email: legal@my-fi.ca
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: calc(72px + var(--spacing-3xl)) 0 var(--spacing-4xl);
  }

  .legal-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
  }

  .legal-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
  }

  .legal-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);
  }

  .legal-section h2 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    padding-top: var(--spacing-lg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-gray-100);
  }

  .legal-section:first-child h2 {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-section h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin: var(--spacing-lg) 0 var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .legal-section p {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .legal-section ul {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    padding-left: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .legal-section li {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    line-height: 1.7;
    list-style-type: disc;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }

  .legal-section li strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .disclaimer-box {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.05), rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.05));
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    margin: var(--spacing-md) 0;
  }

  .disclaimer-box p {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  .disclaimer-box p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
</style>
